\title{discrete topology}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{bradley-et-al-2020}{Bradley et al}{Definition 0.3}

\p{The \em{discrete topology} on a [set](rs-005L) #{X} is the
[topology](rs-00CA) consisting of all [subsets](rs-005N) of #{X}; this forms a
[functor](rs-000L) [\scat{Set}](rs-000C)#{\to} [\scat{Top}](rs-00CA) which is [left
adjoint](rs-0043) to the [forgetful functor](rs-001I).}

